President Obama will be hosting President Juan Manuel Santos of Colombia at the White House on December 3. The visit will focus on highlighting the partnership between the two countries and supporting the Santos Administration's efforts to achieve peace and build a more democratic society. The discussions will cover topics such as citizen security, human rights, and economic prosperity for all Colombians. Additionally, the expansion of economic ties, particularly the U.S.-Colombia Trade Promotion Agreement, will be a key topic of conversation.